io.storj

Class Project

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.storj.Project
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public class Project
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    Represents a stateful resource to a project on a satellite. It allows executing operations on the project like creating, opening, listing, and deleting buckets.

    Make sure to always close the Project object after completing work with it. The Project class implements the AutoCloseable interface, so it is best to use Project objects in try-with-resource blocks:

      try (Uplink uplink = new Uplink();
       Project project = uplink.openProject(scope)) {
      ...
  }
